Terrestrial invertebrates found among marine strandlines or 'wrack beds'
Project
1) Characterize the spatial and temporal variation that occurs in assemblages of invertebrates found on marine strandlines. (2) Examine potential trophic relationships among invertebrates occurring in strandlines. (3) Develop sampling protocol(s) that help portray the high variation that can occur in strandline invertebrate populations due to the spatial and temporal variability of the presence and condition of this ephemeral habitat.
